subSubSection.paragraph:
Carr and Giovannoli (1950)
claimed that ‘a detailed survey of the group [

A.aeneus

] might disclose at least 1 Honduran stock that required naming’. I checked their specimens at UMMZ (see Material examined), and I cannot discern two forms in the area, unless they refer to unmentioned specimens from the upper reaches of the Patuca River, Caribbean drainage, which indeed belong to a different species (

A. belizianus

).
